snippet.textDisplay:
He knew he was coming to an end of what we call life. Better said, he knew he was attracting death to him. You see, we become what we constantly think about. Theres a plentiful of reasons why I am able to express this but the main one is that I fell into coma off of a overdose. Before this, all my thoughts were negative, extremely. I thought about things that brought death and felt lifeless yet I was alive. Some people struggle with their own thoughts and if you cant control them what makes you think you will control your physical body. For some reason(LOVE AND FAITH), I was given a second chance at what we call life. I dont know what Mac was going through but it must have been real painful to the point where he was bonding his pain towards and with substances. He needed a connection. All humans are like this, naturally. We live off of connecting whether you believe it or not. When you see someone or at least feel someone is down, I ask that you reach out with a simple, "How are you feeling"? You are more POWER-FULL than you know and you will all ways make someones day by caring because its simply sharing... your love. Mac wasnt as fortunate as some of us, sadly. Or maybe, it was meant to be like this IDK. (Mac is still here but in a different form of energy, and that is the music he created) Its all about diving deep into your inner self and asking yourself what you really want to be. My message to everyone who reads this is to accept what your reality is, focus on what you have and practice gratitude and finally, be good and do good. Not everyone has what you have. To complete my energy, remember these two phrases:
You are only as safe as your thoughts.
Just keep the faith and you'll be straight!- ESOJ
